  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan announced a class debate today, and the topic was simple: should recess be longer at our school?",
      "zh": "潘老師今天宣布一場班級辯論，題目很簡單：我們學校的下課時間應不應該延長？"
    },
    {
      "en": "He split the class into two groups and told each side to prepare a clear reason and evidence to support their opinion.",
      "zh": "他把全班分成兩組，要求每一邊都準備清楚的理由跟證據來支持自己的立場。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice, on the \"yes\" side, argued that longer recess would have a positive effect on our education, not a negative one.",
      "zh": "站在「贊成」那邊的 Bernice 主張，延長下課時間對我們的教育會有正面影響，而不是負面的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She said students understand new lessons better after a real break, and there is a real possibility that grades would even improve.",
      "zh": "她說學生在真正休息過後對新課程的理解會更好，成績甚至有可能真的進步。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One boy on the \"no\" side objected, saying a shorter school day already has value, since students go home earlier to spend time with family.",
      "zh": "「反對」那邊有個男生表示異議，說較短的在校時間本身就有價值，因為學生能提早回家陪家人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He also mentioned that his older cousin, now studying at a national university, said high-quality study habits matter more than extra playtime.",
      "zh": "他還提到他表哥現在在一所國立大學讀書，說高品質的讀書習慣比多出來的玩耍時間更重要。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Our teacher, acting as a neutral leader for the debate, reminded both sides that in reality, there is rarely one single correct solution.",
      "zh": "我們老師擔任辯論的中立主持人，提醒雙方在現實中很少有單一的正確解答。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, listening from the doorway because his own class had a short break, shouted that his opinion was simply \"longer recess, always,\" which does not count as a real argument.",
      "zh": "從門口聽的 William（因為他自己班上剛好在短暫休息）大喊他的意見就是「下課永遠都要更長」，不過這不算是真正的論點。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan gently reminded us that a good argument needs more than just an independent, personal wish; it needs actual reasoning behind it.",
      "zh": "潘老師溫和地提醒我們，一個好的論點需要的不只是單純個人的希望，還需要真正的推理支撐。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One girl brought up the school's development plan, saying the principal already had a related idea about recess time in progress.",
      "zh": "有個女生提到學校的發展計畫，說校長已經有一個跟下課時間相關的想法正在進行中。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the end of class, no clear winner was chosen, but our teacher said the real goal of a debate is practice, not victory.",
      "zh": "課程結束時沒有明確的勝方，但我們老師說辯論真正的目的是練習，不是輸贏。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice still insists her side technically won, mostly because she was the loudest, which our teacher gently pointed out is not actually how debate works.",
      "zh": "Bernice 還是堅持技術上她那邊贏了，主要是因為她最大聲，我們老師溫和地指出這其實不是辯論的運作方式。"
    }
